trashday.storage

Class DynamoItem

  • java.lang.Object
    • trashday.storage.DynamoItem

  • public class DynamoItem
extends Object
    Class for storing a table item for each application user in a Dynamo DB table. Each item contains the user Schedule and TimeZone data.
    Author:
    J. Todd Baldwin

    • Method Detail

      • getCustomerId

        public String getCustomerId()
        Get the customerId attribute.

        The DynamoDB directive specifies the user's id from Session.getUser() as the primary hash key on the Dynamo DB table when we save this object.

        Returns:
        User's id

      • getCalendar

        public Calendar getCalendar()
        Get the schedule attribute. After DynamoDao.readUserData(trashday.storage.SessionDao) has loaded the correct table item for this user into this object, use this getter to retrieve the Schedule object for this user.

        The DynamoDB directives specify how to serialize the Schedule object into the table's "Data" field.

        Returns:
        User's Schedule

      • getIntentLog

        public IntentLog getIntentLog()
        Get the schedule attribute. After DynamoDao.readUserData(trashday.storage.SessionDao) has loaded the correct table item for this user into this object, use this getter to retrieve the IntentLog object for this user.

        The DynamoDB directives specify how to serialize the IntentLog object into the table's "Data" field.

        Returns:
        User's IntentLog
